This paper deals with the problem of interlinking tables in Wikipedia, which involves information retrieval, natural language processing, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.DB (databases), cs.IR (information retrieval), and cs.CL (computation and language) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a neural-based approach for determining table relations, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.LG (machine learning).
